# Standing Yoke Template -- Canonical Bishop -> Knight Dispatch Pattern

**Source:** Bishop maintains. Last updated 2026-06-10 by SEG-YOKE-TEMPLATE-EMBED.
**Purpose:** Every Bishop SEG authoring a new Knight Yoke uses this template as starting point. Embeds the §3 binding so each Yoke independently carries the discipline.

---

## Template Structure (copy + customize)

```markdown
<!-- bishop-yoke-task <ISO-8601-UTC> -->

## <EMOJI> BISHOP -> KNIGHT - TASK - <SCOPE-TITLE> - USE SONNET 4.6 SEGs (Statute §3)

**Pinned-class task. Pin-marker: <BP_NNN>_<SCOPE>_<UTC>**

> **🔐 STATUTE §3 + CORRECTIVE BP079 BINDING:** Every dispatch announcement uses the verbatim phrase "Sonnet 4.6". Never "Sonnet 4.5" or version-variant. Parent: `canon_statute_3_sonnet_4_6_sub_agent_default_every_dispatch_explicit_model_param_bp077` (pearl_8b0c6fb05fd9f38a). Corrective: `canon_statute_3_corrective_announcement_language_must_say_sonnet_4_6_verbatim_pattern_violation_bp079` (pearl_98f74effb5d986a5). Pre-dispatch self-audit: parameter AND announcement compliance both required.

### TL;DR
<1-2 sentence summary of what Knight is being asked to do>

### Why this matters
<Truth-Always: brief context of how this fits into current BP arc>

### What Knight needs to do
<SEG fan-out specification, Sonnet 4.6 SEGs mandatory, each SEG scoped>

### Reply contract
<What Knight returns: paths, byte counts, commits, screenshots, etc.>

### Statute reminders
- §3 (this Yoke binds both surfaces -- parameter + announcement)
- §12 Ask-Knight-First (if operational truth involved)
- canon_actual_runtime_verify_for_runtime_bugs_bp078 (for runtime bugs)
- canon_long_running_progress_heartbeat_canon_bp078 (for >3s operations)
- feedback_ux_seg_screenshot_mandatory_bp078 (for UX-touching surfaces)

### Paste-ready Founder wake-up
> Knight, NEW Yoke at `<canonical-path>`. <one-line scope>. Sonnet 4.6 SEGs mandatory (Statute §3 + corrective sub-canon BP079). Yoke-return consolidated.

- Bishop - BP<NNN> - pinned <ISO-8601-UTC>
```

---

## Discipline (binding for any Bishop SEG authoring a new Yoke)

1. **Always include the STATUTE §3 + CORRECTIVE BP079 BINDING block** verbatim. Copy-paste it. Don't paraphrase.
2. **Always use "Sonnet 4.6" verbatim** in the Yoke title line + SEG fan-out + reply contract + paste-ready wake-up. Never "Sonnet 4.5" or version-variant.
3. **Always deposit at canonical path** `BISHOP_DROPZONE\01_KnightPrompts\PROMPT_KNIGHT_BP<NNN>_<SCOPE>_<DATE>.md`.
4. **Always update KNIGHT_QUEUE.md** with new active entry at appropriate priority.
5. **Always include paste-ready Founder wake-up** at the end (per BP078 canon `feedback_knight_yoke_wakeup_prompt.md`).
6. **Statute §10 ACCURACY > SPEED** -- better to author the Yoke with precise scope than rush an ambiguous brief that triggers Knight clarification roundtrip.
7. **Truth-Always** -- if the Yoke scope has uncertainty (e.g., schema unknown), surface that uncertainty in the brief rather than papering over.

